george earl trenkle, 40, of blackfoot, idaho, was presumed drowned after a saturday boating accident in which he and two others were thrown from their driftboat
his son, george edward trenkle, 18, said their driftboat hit a log and capsized. the elder trenkle gave up his life preserver to save his son's life, then was carried by the current around a bend
the third man, roland parkhurst, 40, of gresham, was wearing a life jacket. he and the younger trenkle were rescued by witnesses
a multnomah county river patrol crew searched the bank and surface for trenkle's body saturday, sunday and monday. deputy garr nielsen said nothing was found and that the search would continue
