spring thunderstorms spawned tornadoes and pounded oklahoma with hail and winds gusting to 75 mph that destroyed a mobile home, killing a woman, while in utah a snowstorm was blamed for a fatal car-train collision
frigid air followed the storm that hit utah on monday, and the national weather service warned fruit farmers the low temperatures could hurt crops today
thunderstorms swept through central, eastern and southwestern oklahoma on monday
a tornado touched down in southwest oklahoma city, and unconfirmed tornadoes were reported in nearby mustang, harrah and midwest city. another touched down just northwest of little rock, ark
in oklahoma city, high winds destroyed a mobile home in the sherwood homes trailer park, said authorities, who could not confirm reports of a tornado
lillian robinson, 69, was dead on arrival at midwest city hospital, an unidentified spokesman said. her husband, who was not identified, was hospitalized in serious condition
the wind shoved some mobile homes off their foundations and shook others, said trailer park resident mike mcfarland
it was a very loud noise,'' mcfarland said
high winds also threw half a dozen trailers onto their sides at a trailer company in oklahoma city, and damaged roofs on city hall, a fast food restaurant and a funeral home in mustang, officials said
