americans who pay at least $100 can have the names of their immigrant ancestors inscribed on a plaque on a wall. the names also will be stored in a computer, along with the person's nation of origin
ellis island is a milestone of american history,'' miss loren, a french citizen who was born in italy, said during her visit monday
she was accompanied by chrysler corp. chairman lee iacocca, who said the foundation needs $15 million to $20 million to complete renovation of the immigration station as a museum and conference center
