however, said the source, both men are concerned because the justice department's image continues to be damaged due to the ongoing criminal investigation of meese, the nation's top law enforcement officer
terry eastland, a justice department spokesman, pointed out that it is not unusual for political appointees to leave government in the last year of an administration
eastland said that burns, weld and stephen s. trott, the associate attorney general who was confirmed as a federal judge last week, were sworn into their jobs in 1986 and that ``this is 1988; this happens to be a year when people are leaving and they all happen to be leaving at the same time.''
the department has not replaced trott
